What is a Linked List?
A Linked List is a data structure where each element (node) is linked to the next.
 Unlike an array, linked lists donâ€™t store elements in contiguous memory locations.

ğŸ“Œ Key Features of Linked List:
âœ… Dynamic Size: Unlike arrays, they grow/shrink dynamically.
âœ… Efficient Insertions/Deletions: No need to shift elements like arrays.
âŒ No Direct Access: Cannot access an element directly using an index.

Types of Linked Lists
1ï¸âƒ£ Singly Linked List (Each node has data + next)
2ï¸âƒ£ Doubly Linked List (Each node has data + next + prev)
